```python
import openpyxl

def read_spreadsheet(filepath):
    wb = openpyxl.load_workbook(filepath)
    
    # Get the first sheet in the workbook
    sheet = wb.active
    
    # Iterate through each row and column in the sheet
    for row in sheet.iter_rows():
        for cell in row:
            print(cell.value, end=" ")  # Print the value of the cell
        print()  # Move to next line after printing all cells in a row
```

This function will read from a spreadsheet and print its contents. You can replace `print()` with other actions such as storing the data in a list or dictionary for further processing.
